title: Omar al-Bashir - Wikipedia
snippet: From December 2018 onwards, al-Bashir faced large-scale protests which demanded his removal from power. On 11 April 2019, Bashir was ousted in a military coup d'état.

title: 2019 Sudanese coup d'état - Wikipedia
snippet: A coup d'état took place in Sudan in the late afternoon on 11 April 2019, when President Omar al-Bashir was overthrown by the Sudanese Armed Forces after popular protests demanded his departure.

title: Removal of President Omar al-Bashir and the Continued Pursuit of Justice - United States Holocaust Memorial Museum
snippet: In April 2019 he was removed from office, and by August a civilian-military transitional government had formed. Since then, the difficult process of forming a new government has continued.

title: Omar al-Bashir | Alive, Now, Overthrown, Trial, Biography & Facts | Britannica
snippet: He served as president from 1993 until he was overthrown in 2019. The International Criminal Court issued an arrest warrant for him, charging him with various crimes related to the crisis in Darfur.

title: Omar al-Bashir: Sudan's ousted president - BBC News
snippet: Sudan's ousted President Omar al-Bashir's career has been defined by war. He came to power in a military coup in 1989 and ruled what was until 2011 Africa's largest country with an iron fist.
